{"application": "software-mentions", "version": "0.8.0", "date": "2024-10-07T11:40+0000", "md5": "C4775083ED83D9522C73F721AED52338", "mentions": [{"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "hypernym", "normalizedForm": "hypernym", "offsetStart": 8, "offsetEnd": 16}, "context": "Predict hypernym: <A> audio feedback input arrangements for interaction between user and computer input arrangements for interaction between player and computer user input interfaces for electrophonic musical instruments ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.019947528839111328}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 1.5735626220703125e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999886751174927}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9992794394493103}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.987022399902344e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "hypernym", "normalizedForm": "hypernym", "offsetStart": 19, "offsetEnd": 27}, "context": "Among the 200 term-hypernym candidates, we noticed 11 problematic expressions, 4 of which are incorrect for long expressions because of the attachment step III, as an example of the detected problems consider \"methods or arrangements for sensing record carriers by electromagnetic radiation sensing by electromagnetic radiation sensing by radiation using wavelengths larger than 0.1 mm arrangements for protecting the arrangement comprising a circuit inside of the interrogation device\".", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.998633086681366}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 5.245208740234375e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.5762786865234375e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999886751174927}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9992794394493103}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.987022399902344e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "hypernym", "normalizedForm": "hypernym", "offsetStart": 20, "offsetEnd": 28}, "context": "Other approaches to hypernym prediction were primitively designed for knowledge base completion, where hypernym is considered as one of the semantic relations between two nodes in a graph.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.001463770866394043}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0029715895652770996}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999886751174927}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9992794394493103}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.987022399902344e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "hypernym", "normalizedForm": "hypernym", "offsetStart": 34, "offsetEnd": 42}, "context": "(Cho et al., 2020) formulated the hypernym prediction as a sequence generation task, they trained an LSTM-based model to predict the hypernym of the given input or the previous prediction in the output sequence.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9975862503051758}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.01838386058807373}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999886751174927}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9992794394493103}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.987022399902344e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "hypernym", "normalizedForm": "hypernym", "offsetStart": 45, "offsetEnd": 53}, "context": "However, none of them were interested in the hypernym or hyponym relations between technological expressions.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.990156888961792}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00012743473052978516}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.5762786865234375e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999886751174927}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9992794394493103}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.987022399902344e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "PyTorch", "normalizedForm": "PyTorch", "offsetStart": 48, "offsetEnd": 55}, "context": "We fine-tuned the t5-base9 seq2seq model in its PyTorch version from huggingface for hypernyms /hyponyms prediction with the following hyperparameter settings: optimizer = AdamW, learning rate = 1e-4, max length = 128, batch size = 16, and number of epochs = 6. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9991263747215271}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 1.430511474609375e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9991263747215271}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 1.430511474609375e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "hypernym", "normalizedForm": "hypernym", "offsetStart": 49, "offsetEnd": 57}, "context": "Experimentally, the system has proved useful for hypernym/hyponym retrieval, as well as for other text mining and information retrieval tasks for patent or scientific texts.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 4.1604042053222656e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.03480494022369385}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.5762786865234375e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999886751174927}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9992794394493103}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.987022399902344e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "hypernym", "normalizedForm": "hypernym", "offsetStart": 49, "offsetEnd": 57}, "context": "For the dataset, we extracted and mixed all term-hypernym pairs from each domain, and then split the training and test data at a ratio of 0.8 and 0.2.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999886751174927}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 6.794929504394531e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999886751174927}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9992794394493103}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.987022399902344e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "hypernym", "normalizedForm": "hypernym", "offsetStart": 54, "offsetEnd": 62}, "context": "The input format of the T5 model is fixed as \"predict hypernym: \" / \"predict hyponym: \" + <special token of domain> + term expression.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.004041731357574463}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 5.7220458984375e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.5762786865234375e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999886751174927}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9992794394493103}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.987022399902344e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "hypernym", "normalizedForm": "hypernym", "offsetStart": 70, "offsetEnd": 78}, "context": "However, pre-trained generation models have yet to be explored in the hypernym prediction task.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00024515390396118164}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.45259082317352295}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999886751174927}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9992794394493103}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.987022399902344e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "hypernym", "normalizedForm": "hypernym", "offsetStart": 75, "offsetEnd": 83}, "context": "The T5 model opens the taxonomy to any new technological terms for which a hypernym can be generated, thus making the resource updateable with new terms, an essential feature for the constantly evolving field of technological terminology.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 6.270408630371094e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.09629285335540771}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999886751174927}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9992794394493103}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.987022399902344e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "hypernym", "normalizedForm": "hypernym", "offsetStart": 77, "offsetEnd": 85}, "context": "Concerning semantic relations, 170 of the 200 pairs can be qualified as term-hypernym pairs, which is a precision of 85%.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.004816710948944092}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 2.5510787963867188e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999886751174927}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9992794394493103}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.987022399902344e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "hypernym", "normalizedForm": "hypernym", "offsetStart": 96, "offsetEnd": 104}, "context": "Early approaches such as (Weeds et al., 2014) and (Vyas and Carpuat, 2017) consider the task of hypernym prediction as a binary classification (hypernym detection) of whether two given words or multi-word expressions are in a hypernym relation.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00010073184967041016}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0530053973197937}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 5.960464477539062e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999886751174927}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9992794394493103}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.987022399902344e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "hypernym", "normalizedForm": "hypernym", "offsetStart": 98, "offsetEnd": 106}, "context": "We do not discuss related research about hyponym prediction because 1) it is a symmetric task for hypernym prediction; 2) hypernym prediction is easier to be formulated mathematically since each entity should have only one hypernym in a well-defined taxonomy.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0003267526626586914}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.06686174869537354}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.152557373046875e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999886751174927}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9992794394493103}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.987022399902344e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "hypernym", "normalizedForm": "hypernym", "offsetStart": 100, "offsetEnd": 108}, "context": "Therefore, we decided to create a CPC-based taxonomy, specifically designed for the task of hyponym/hypernym retrieval of patent texts, which shares a large number of words with real patents and can be automatically updated every year.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00010478496551513672}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9992794394493103}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999886751174927}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9992794394493103}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.987022399902344e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "hypernym", "normalizedForm": "hypernym", "offsetStart": 103, "offsetEnd": 111}, "context": "Other approaches to hypernym prediction were primitively designed for knowledge base completion, where hypernym is considered as one of the semantic relations between two nodes in a graph.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.001463770866394043}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0029715895652770996}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999886751174927}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9992794394493103}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.987022399902344e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Prot\u00e9g\u00e9", "normalizedForm": "Prot\u00e9g\u00e9", "offsetStart": 108, "offsetEnd": 115}, "context": "In addition, we will try to convert and preserve our taxonomies in specialized ontological software such as Prot\u00e9g\u00e9.1", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0007275938987731934}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9132415652275085}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.5762786865234375e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0007275938987731934}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9132415652275085}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.5762786865234375e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "hypernym", "normalizedForm": "hypernym", "offsetStart": 122, "offsetEnd": 130}, "context": "We do not discuss related research about hyponym prediction because 1) it is a symmetric task for hypernym prediction; 2) hypernym prediction is easier to be formulated mathematically since each entity should have only one hypernym in a well-defined taxonomy.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0003267526626586914}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.06686174869537354}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.152557373046875e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999886751174927}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9992794394493103}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.987022399902344e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "hypernym", "normalizedForm": "hypernym", "offsetStart": 123, "offsetEnd": 131}, "context": "After applying the data pre-processing and title2term algorithm on titles of each domain section, the total number of term-hypernym pairs we have is as in Table 2.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9852235317230225}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 2.7418136596679688e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999886751174927}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9992794394493103}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.987022399902344e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "hypernym", "normalizedForm": "hypernym", "offsetStart": 133, "offsetEnd": 141}, "context": "(Cho et al., 2020) formulated the hypernym prediction as a sequence generation task, they trained an LSTM-based model to predict the hypernym of the given input or the previous prediction in the output sequence.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9975862503051758}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.01838386058807373}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999886751174927}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9992794394493103}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.987022399902344e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "hypernym", "normalizedForm": "hypernym", "offsetStart": 144, "offsetEnd": 152}, "context": "Early approaches such as (Weeds et al., 2014) and (Vyas and Carpuat, 2017) consider the task of hypernym prediction as a binary classification (hypernym detection) of whether two given words or multi-word expressions are in a hypernym relation.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00010073184967041016}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0530053973197937}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 5.960464477539062e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999886751174927}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9992794394493103}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.987022399902344e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "hypernym", "normalizedForm": "hypernym", "offsetStart": 148, "offsetEnd": 156}, "context": "Among the errors, more than half are pairs of an instance and a process or action (e.g., \"Testing, calibrating, or compensating of compasses\" whose hypernym is not really the proposed \"Compasses\"); other cases involve problematic expressions and inversions of the relation (term pairs should be in a hypernym relation but is in a hyponym relation) such as \"Saddling equipment for riding or pack-animals\" being the hyponym of \"STIRRUPS\".", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8050728440284729}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 3.5762786865234375e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 5.960464477539062e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999886751174927}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9992794394493103}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.987022399902344e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "hypernym", "normalizedForm": "hypernym", "offsetStart": 181, "offsetEnd": 189}, "context": "In our study, we explore the seq2seq pretrained language generation model T5 (Text-to-Text Transfer Transformer) (Raffel et al., 2020) to test its transfer learning capabilities in hypernym discovery.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0005002021789550781}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.999064028263092}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999886751174927}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9992794394493103}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.987022399902344e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "hypernym", "normalizedForm": "hypernym", "offsetStart": 205, "offsetEnd": 213}, "context": "To conclude, in this paper we have shown how the well-curated patent classification system CPC can be used as a resource for developing 1) an open highquality taxonomy of technical terms and 2) a T5-based hypernym generator that allows for validation of the coherence of the taxonomy as well as for hypernym/hyponym generation.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00045752525329589844}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9877148866653442}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.987022399902344e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999886751174927}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9992794394493103}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.987022399902344e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "hypernym", "normalizedForm": "hypernym", "offsetStart": 223, "offsetEnd": 231}, "context": "We do not discuss related research about hyponym prediction because 1) it is a symmetric task for hypernym prediction; 2) hypernym prediction is easier to be formulated mathematically since each entity should have only one hypernym in a well-defined taxonomy.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0003267526626586914}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.06686174869537354}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.152557373046875e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999886751174927}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9992794394493103}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.987022399902344e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "hypernym", "normalizedForm": "hypernym", "offsetStart": 226, "offsetEnd": 234}, "context": "Early approaches such as (Weeds et al., 2014) and (Vyas and Carpuat, 2017) consider the task of hypernym prediction as a binary classification (hypernym detection) of whether two given words or multi-word expressions are in a hypernym relation.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00010073184967041016}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0530053973197937}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 5.960464477539062e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999886751174927}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9992794394493103}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.987022399902344e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "hypernym", "normalizedForm": "hypernym", "offsetStart": 267, "offsetEnd": 275}, "context": "Later solutions such as (Yamane et al., 2016), (Ustalov et al., 2017), and (Bernier-Colborne and Barri\u00e8re, 2018) proposed supervised projection learning methods to learn multiple matrices that project a query embedding such that the projection is close to its target hypernym.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0001043081283569336}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.2787282466888428}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999886751174927}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9992794394493103}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.987022399902344e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "hypernym", "normalizedForm": "hypernym", "offsetStart": 299, "offsetEnd": 307}, "context": "To conclude, in this paper we have shown how the well-curated patent classification system CPC can be used as a resource for developing 1) an open highquality taxonomy of technical terms and 2) a T5-based hypernym generator that allows for validation of the coherence of the taxonomy as well as for hypernym/hyponym generation.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00045752525329589844}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9877148866653442}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.987022399902344e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999886751174927}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9992794394493103}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.987022399902344e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "hypernym", "normalizedForm": "hypernym", "offsetStart": 300, "offsetEnd": 308}, "context": "Among the errors, more than half are pairs of an instance and a process or action (e.g., \"Testing, calibrating, or compensating of compasses\" whose hypernym is not really the proposed \"Compasses\"); other cases involve problematic expressions and inversions of the relation (term pairs should be in a hypernym relation but is in a hyponym relation) such as \"Saddling equipment for riding or pack-animals\" being the hyponym of \"STIRRUPS\".", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8050728440284729}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 3.5762786865234375e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 5.960464477539062e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999886751174927}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9992794394493103}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.987022399902344e-06}}}], "references": [], "runtime": 11102, "id": "a041c200cfe69